f(x,y) = ((((x + y) ^ (2 / x)) * ((~x) / (x ^ 18))) | (((y % 6) ^ (x & y)) &
((-x) + (x | y)))) % 5

Extent: 256x256 (scaled x2)

"Onebit" colouring scheme.
account:
{'id': 166157, 'username': 'bitartbot', 'acct': 'bitartbot@botsin.space', 'display_name': 'Bit Art Bot', 'locked': False, 'bot': True, 'discoverable': True, 'group': False, 'created_at': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 4, 0, 0, tzinfo=tzutc()), 'note': '

This is a bot which produces procedural art by plotting an integer function taking the current coordinates and producing an integer result. The function is procedurally created using random numbers and appears in the status text.

Coordinates are coloured either by where the value appears within the range of results (the "gradient" scheme) or simply by whether it is the most common result (white) or not (black) (the "onebit" scheme.)

The code does not resort to evaluating a string.

content:
So apparently Switzerland (landlord association) is debating putting forward
legislation that would limit the living space of people.

If implemented it would mean that, if you're living alone, the "most space"
you are legally allowed to rent / live in, would be a two-room apartment.

So if you have kids that move out, you are potentially no longer allowed to
live in your flat. If someone in your family dies? Well, better look for a new
flat.

Capitalism is hell.

content:
Reading Armstrong on her daughter saying Mama:

"This is simultaneously heartwarming and heart-wrenching because, hey! You
know who I am. Except, rarely do you ever say Mama as if you are going to
follow that word with something nice like, My! How you smell like a flower!
Instead you say it like a beer-bellied construction worker who wants his
dinner now, and so he screams, 'WOMAN! Bring me them there pork rinds!' The
part where he says WOMAN, that's how you say Mama.

((-x) + (x | y)))) % 5

Extent: 256x256 (scaled x2)

"Onebit" colouring scheme.
account:
{'id': 166157, 'username': 'bitartbot', 'acct': 'bitartbot@botsin.space', 'display_name': 'Bit Art Bot', 'locked': False, 'bot': True, 'discoverable': True, 'group': False, 'created_at': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 4, 0, 0, tzinfo=tzutc()), 'note': '

This is a bot which produces procedural art by plotting an integer function taking the current coordinates and producing an integer result. The function is procedurally created using random numbers and appears in the status text.

Coordinates are coloured either by where the value appears within the range of results (the "gradient" scheme) or simply by whether it is the most common result (white) or not (black) (the "onebit" scheme.)

The code does not resort to evaluating a string.

[#Sindelfingen](https://mastodon.social/tags/Sindelfingen) ‚Äì Zwei Tote nach
Sch√ºssen auf Mercedes-Benz-Gel√§nde

Bei Sch√ºssen auf einem Werksgel√§nde von Mercedes-Benz in Sindelfingen sind
zwei Menschen get√∂tet worden. Laut Polizei wurde der mutma√üliche T√§ter

content:
So apparently Switzerland (landlord association) is debating putting forward
legislation that would limit the living space of people.

If implemented it would mean that, if you're living alone, the "most space"
you are legally allowed to rent / live in, would be a two-room apartment.

So if you have kids that move out, you are potentially no longer allowed to
live in your flat. If someone in your family dies? Well, better look for a new
flat.

Capitalism is hell.

content:
Reading Armstrong on her daughter saying Mama:

"This is simultaneously heartwarming and heart-wrenching because, hey! You
know who I am. Except, rarely do you ever say Mama as if you are going to
follow that word with something nice like, My! How you smell like a flower!
Instead you say it like a beer-bellied construction worker who wants his
dinner now, and so he screams, 'WOMAN! Bring me them there pork rinds!' The
part where he says WOMAN, that's how you say Mama.

((-x) + (x | y)))) % 5

Extent: 256x256 (scaled x2)

"Onebit" colouring scheme.
account:
{'id': 166157, 'username': 'bitartbot', 'acct': 'bitartbot@botsin.space', 'display_name': 'Bit Art Bot', 'locked': False, 'bot': True, 'discoverable': True, 'group': False, 'created_at': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 4, 0, 0, tzinfo=tzutc()), 'note': '

This is a bot which produces procedural art by plotting an integer function taking the current coordinates and producing an integer result. The function is procedurally created using random numbers and appears in the status text.

Coordinates are coloured either by where the value appears within the range of results (the "gradient" scheme) or simply by whether it is the most common result (white) or not (black) (the "onebit" scheme.)

The code does not resort to evaluating a string.

content:
So apparently Switzerland (landlord association) is debating putting forward
legislation that would limit the living space of people.

If implemented it would mean that, if you're living alone, the "most space"
you are legally allowed to rent / live in, would be a two-room apartment.

So if you have kids that move out, you are potentially no longer allowed to
live in your flat. If someone in your family dies? Well, better look for a new
flat.

Capitalism is hell.

content:
Reading Armstrong on her daughter saying Mama:

"This is simultaneously heartwarming and heart-wrenching because, hey! You
know who I am. Except, rarely do you ever say Mama as if you are going to
follow that word with something nice like, My! How you smell like a flower!
Instead you say it like a beer-bellied construction worker who wants his
dinner now, and so he screams, 'WOMAN! Bring me them there pork rinds!' The
part where he says WOMAN, that's how you say Mama.
